.TH GIRLFRIEND 1 "May 2026" "girlfriend 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
girlfriend \- funny romantic Linux terminal companion

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B girlfriend
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Girlfriend is a funny offline terminal companion for Linux users.
It provides romantic jokes, nerdy compliments, ASCII art,
notifications, voice mode, and meme-style interactions.

Designed for Debian, Ubuntu, Kali Linux, and other Linux distributions.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B girlfriend
Display a random romantic or funny message.

.TP
.B girlfriend compliment
Show a nerdy compliment.

.TP
.B girlfriend roast
Display a harmless funny roast.

.TP
.B girlfriend ascii
Show cute ASCII art.

.TP
.B girlfriend streak
Display interaction streak statistics.

.TP
.B girlfriend speak
Read messages aloud using espeak.

.TP
.B girlfriend help
Show help information.

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B --mood caring
Use caring personality mode.

.TP
.B --mood hacker
Use hacker-themed responses.

.TP
.B --mood clingy
Use clingy personality mode.

.TP
.B --mood gamer
Use gaming-themed responses.

.TP
.B --version
Display application version.

.TP
.B --help
Display help information.

.SH CONFIG DIRECTORY

Configuration and local data are stored in:

.B ~/.girlfriend/

Files may include:

.TP
config.json
Application configuration.

.TP
streak.json
User streak statistics.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
Run default mode:
.B girlfriend

.TP
Show compliment:
.B girlfriend compliment

.TP
Run hacker mood:
.B girlfriend --mood hacker

.TP
Show ASCII art:
.B girlfriend ascii

.TP
Enable voice output:
.B girlfriend speak

.SH AUTHOR
Created for Linux users who needed emotional support during terminal sessions.

